      <p>
          Suppose a bank gives out a number of loans.  Each of the  <m>4</m>  loans has a <m>0.23</m> chance of  defaulting.  Suppose that whether or not each  loan  default is independent of the other  loans.  Find the following:
      </p>
      
      
      <p>
          <ol>
              <li>
                  What is the probability that <m>2</m>  loans  default?
              </li>
             
              <li>
                  What is the probability that <m>3</m>  loans  default?
              </li>
              
              
              <li>
                  What is the probability that  greater than  <m>3</m>  loans  default?
              </li>
              
              <li>
                  What is the probability that between <m>1</m> and <m>2</m> (inclusive)  loans  default?
              </li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
